[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_6ges8")
reagent_id = "NH4OH"
title = "Ammonium hydroxide"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]NH₄OH[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]35 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State:[/cell][cell]Aqueous solution (ammonia dissolved in water)[/cell]
[cell]Type:[/cell][cell]Weak base[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reaction[/b]
NH₃ + H₂O → NH₄OH
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Formed when ammonia dissolves in water.  
• Has a strong ammonia smell.  
• Produces alkaline solutions.
[b]Where ammonium hydroxide is found[/b]
• In cleaning solutions.  
• In laboratories and industry.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Household cleaners.  
• Production of fertilizers and chemicals.  
• Used in laboratory reactions.
[b]Safety[/b]
Irritating to skin, eyes, and lungs.  
Vapors should not be inhaled."
